took this photo right after having existential conversation riding round malibu w @blairbbrown and @bagelbiteskevin about modern anxiety and how constantly having everything at our fingertips and the constant pressure to publicize your life causes this lack of true connection and an increasing sense of “everyone knows what you’re doing but no ones knows how you’re doing” (courtesy to @adrianamariek for this quote lol). but then again here i am contributing to it. life today is funny...i guess all we can do is try to use these opportunities to create real conversation and connection that last beyond a passing like and comment. love y’all 💕
~HOW I’M FEELING~ MARCH 6TH

when i was asked to be the cover of this month's @gaytimes, first and foremost, i was honored to join the ranks of LGBT icons and allies such boy george, laverne cox, lizzo, billy porter and dan reynolds. i’m humbled to have the opportunity to use my platform to support something i so deeply believe in: which is being fully yourself, embracing that, and celebrating that along with the world, no matter who you are and who you love. on the other hand, i felt guilty taking up space in a community that deserves to have its own members spotlighted. since i started making music and experimenting with style and self expression, so much of what i do today is inspired by queer trailblazers, friends and collaborators. i hope you guys see this cover as support for a community i truly love and admire — i wouldn’t be where i am today without you.⁣

something that came up today in my meditation..i was caught up in fear, indulging in negative thoughts, but then something clicked: i realized that these thoughts weren’t necessarily the truth. they were just a voice. a voice built out of habit...i’ve learned that so much of our unhappiness is caused by habitual thinking..thoughts that feel like home, but that don’t serve us. thoughts that feel like the truth, but that really aren’t. once you realize this, you can learn how to detach yourself and move on with your life. this is where you grow and this is where you find freedom and happiness. it’s all right there waiting for you. i promise. 💛
